GOOD. JENNY'S
STARTING TO GET NEEDY.

00:45.300 --> 00:46.567
TELL YOU SOMETHING, CORY,

00:46.567 --> 00:51.100
AT A CERTAIN AGE, YOU ARE AFRAID
TO GO TO SLEEP AT NIGHT.

00:51.100 --> 00:52.967
I'LL TELL YOU
SOMETHING ELSE, ERIC,

00:52.967 --> 00:54.033
YOU HIT A CERTAIN AGE,

00:54.033 --> 00:56.967
YOU'RE AFRAID TO WAKE UP
IN THE MORNING.

00:59.500 --> 01:01.734
YOU'RE AVOIDING
THE MIRROR AGAIN.

01:01.734 --> 01:03.133
NO, I'M NOT.

01:03.133 --> 01:04.667
LISTEN TO ME, CORY.
SOONER OR LATER,

01:04.667 --> 01:08.100
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO LOOK
AT YOURSELF, MY FRIEND.
COME ON.

01:09.600 --> 01:11.800
AW, MAN. IT'S ME.

01:11.800 --> 01:12.934
COME ON, COR.

01:12.934 --> 01:15.800
EVERY TEENAGER GOES
THROUGH THIS GAWKY, AWKWARD,

01:15.800 --> 01:17.100
HATE-WHAT-THEY-LOOK-LIKE
PHASE.

01:17.100 --> 01:18.100
WELL, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

01:18.100 --> 01:19.567
YEAH, YOU THINK THAT, BABY.

01:19.567 --> 01:21.200
LISTEN TO ME.
WHY DON'T WE STICK

01:21.200 --> 01:23.200
WITH THE PROBLEM THAT IS
YOUR HEAD, ALL RIGHT,
MY FRIEND?

01:23.200 --> 01:24.233
NOW, FOR
THE NEXT FEW YEARS,

01:24.233 --> 01:25.300
YOU'RE GONNA BE GROWING
INTO YOUR LOOK.

01:25.300 --> 01:26.500
EVERYBODY UNDERSTANDS THAT.

01:26.500 --> 01:29.033
NOBODY'S GONNA GIVE YOU
A HARD TIME ABOUT IT, OK?

01:29.033 --> 01:31.900
HI, I'M CORY, AND FOR
THE NEXT THREE YEARS,

01:31.900 --> 01:34.200
I'M GONNA LOOK
LIKE A POTATO.

01:34.200 --> 01:35.300
MORGAN, YOU WANNA
GET OUT OF HERE?

01:35.300 --> 01:38.567
NO. THE CHILD
SPEAKS THE TRUTH.

01:38.567 --> 01:42.700
I, CORY MATTHEWS,
AM A PO-TA-TO.

01:53.934 --> 01:56.467
I'LL JUST TAKE THAT,
MR. MATTHEWS.

01:56.467 --> 01:58.500
NOW I GOT NO PIPE.

01:59.567 --> 02:00.900
YES. FINE.
YOU'RE PERFECT.

02:00.900 --> 02:03.600
NOW, CAN WE GET
OUT OF THE HALLWAY
WHERE EVERYONE CAN SEE ME?

02:03.600 --> 02:07.033
HOLD ON. JUST NEED
TO GET A LITTLE MORE
HAIR IN MY EYES.

02:07.033 --> 02:09.800
YOU KNOW I HATE THAT.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.600
ALSO GOOD.

02:12.600 --> 02:15.000
ALSO GOOD.
ALSO GOOD. MOVE!

02:15.000 --> 02:17.000
WHAT? WHAT?
CORY, CORY.
COME ON. COME ON.

02:17.000 --> 02:18.200
YOU'RE GONNA
CUT YOUR FINGERS.

02:18.200 --> 02:19.500
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M OVERREACTING.

02:19.500 --> 02:22.133
IT'S JUST THAT
BETWEEN YOU AND ERIC,

02:22.133 --> 02:25.500
I FEEL LIKE I'M SURROUNDED
BY PEOPLE WITH PERFECT HAIR.

02:25.500 --> 02:26.600
HI, CORY.

02:26.600 --> 02:29.500
NO NEED TO EXPLAIN
THIS RELATIONSHIP, IS THERE?

02:29.500 --> 02:30.600
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
TALKING ABOUT?

02:30.600 --> 02:33.300
NOTHING. I'M JUST
A LITTLE INSECURE TODAY,

02:33.300 --> 02:34.867
BUT I'M SURE IT WILL PASS.

02:34.867 --> 02:35.867
HEY, TOPANGA.

02:35.867 --> 02:36.867
HEY, DYLAN.

02:36.867 --> 02:38.233
SO, YOU WANNA GO OUT
THIS WEEKEND?

02:38.233 --> 02:40.500
OF COURSE NOT.
I'M GOING OUT WITH CORY.

02:40.500 --> 02:41.700
OH. YOU'RE
STILL WITH HIM?

02:41.700 --> 02:43.767
I FIGURED YOU'D HAVE
DUMPED HIM OVER THE SUMMER.

02:43.767 --> 02:45.133
WOULD YOU PLEASE LEAVE?

02:45.133 --> 02:49.200
YEAH, BUT IF YOU DO
DECIDE TO DUMP HIM,
HERE'S MY CARD.

02:49.200 --> 02:52.500
"LOCKER NUMBER 168."

02:52.500 --> 02:54.967
HA. THAT'S
A NICE LOCKER.

02:54.967 --> 02:59.200
LOOK, CORY, IT'S JUST
SOME GUY ASKING ME OUT.
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

02:59.200 --> 03:00.500
WELL, IT'S NO BIG DEAL
TO YOU

03:00.500 --> 03:01.800
BECAUSE YOU'RE THE ASKEE.

03:01.800 --> 03:03.000
AND WHY ARE YOU
THE ASKEE?

03:03.000 --> 03:05.734
YOU'RE ALWAYS THE ASKEE
BECAUSE YOU ARE GORGEOUS.

03:05.734 --> 03:06.800
WELL, THANK YOU
VERY MUCH,

03:06.800 --> 03:08.100
BUT GIVE ME
SOME CREDIT.

03:08.100 --> 03:10.500
I KNOW GUYS GO OUT
WITH GIRLS BECAUSE
OF HOW THEY LOOK.

03:10.500 --> 03:14.567
BUT YOU GO OUT WITH ME
BECAUSE OF WHO I AM INSIDE.

03:15.967 --> 03:18.100
THE ONLY REASON YOU THINK
I'M GOOD-LOOKING

03:18.100 --> 03:20.100
IS BECAUSE
YOU CARE ABOUT ME.

03:21.700 --> 03:23.400
THAT WAS
ONE TOO MANY.

03:23.400 --> 03:25.734
IT WOULDN'T MATTER
WHAT I LOOKED LIKE. YOU'D
STILL THINK I WAS PRETTY.

03:25.734 --> 03:27.900
YEAH, BUT, TOPANGA,
I MEAN, THIS IS EASY
FOR YOU TO SAY.

03:27.900 --> 03:30.400
YOU DON'T HAVE A NOSE
THAT TAKES UP
HALF YOUR FACE

03:30.400 --> 03:32.200
AND HAIR
LIKE A BRILLO PAD.

03:32.200 --> 03:33.934
COME HERE.

03:33.934 --> 03:35.300
WHAT? YA SAW SUDS?

03:35.300 --> 03:40.367
FIRST OF ALL,
I LOVE YOUR FACE,
AND I LOVE YOUR HAIR,

03:40.367 --> 03:41.400
BUT MOST OF ALL,

03:41.400 --> 03:43.834
I LOVE YOU
BECAUSE OF WHO YOU ARE.

03:43.834 --> 03:46.900
AND I HOPE YOU LOVE ME
BECAUSE OF WHO I AM

03:46.900 --> 03:49.500
AND NOT BECAUSE
OF MY FACE AND HAIR.

03:49.500 --> 03:51.233
CORY.

03:51.233 --> 03:53.400
TOPANGA, IF I LOOKED IN
THE MIRROR EVERY MORNING

03:53.400 --> 03:56.233
AND SAW WHAT YOU SEE,
I'D FEEL REAL GOOD
ABOUT MYSELF, TOO.

03:56.233 --> 03:57.700
OH, SO YOU THINK
THAT'S IT?

03:57.700 --> 04:00.200
YOU THINK WHAT GIVES ME
ALL MY CONFIDENCE
IS MY FACE AND HAIR.

04:00.200 --> 04:01.467
AND THE FACT
THAT THEY'RE PERFECT,

04:01.467 --> 04:03.500
YEAH, I THINK THAT
PUTS A LITTLE SPRING
IN YOUR STEP.

04:03.500 --> 04:05.100
OH, YEAH?

04:05.100 --> 04:07.000
WELL, HERE'S
WHAT I THINK.

04:07.000 --> 04:09.033
WORDS, TOPANGA.
USE YOUR WORDS.

04:12.800 --> 04:13.800
WELL?

04:13.800 --> 04:16.500
AM I ANY DIFFERENT NOW?

04:17.600 --> 04:19.467
WELL, SOMEWHAT
LESS PREDICTABLE,

04:19.467 --> 04:20.600
BUT, NO,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.900
I'D LOVE YOU
NO MATTER WHAT
YOU LOOKED LIKE.

04:22.900 --> 04:26.834
GOOD. GLAD YOU
LEARNED SOMETHING.

04:32.734 --> 04:34.000
SHE'S GONNA SCREAM NOW.

04:34.000 --> 04:35.467
AAH!

04:38.000 --> 04:39.734
IT'S OK.
IT'S JUST A LITTLE HAIR.

04:39.734 --> 04:40.967
IT HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH WHO I AM.

04:40.967 --> 04:42.200
I AM STILL
TOPANGA LAWRENCE,

04:42.200 --> 04:45.900
AND NOBODY WHO CARES ABOUT
ME WILL EVEN NOTICE, RIGHT?

04:45.900 --> 04:47.367
MR. MATTHEWS.

04:47.367 --> 04:48.400
MR. HUNTER.

04:48.400 --> 04:49.400
OOH.

04:49.400 --> 04:51.400
WHAT THE HECK
HAPPENED TO YOU?

04:51.400 --> 04:52.467
MR. FEENY,
I'VE CUT MY HAIR

04:52.467 --> 04:53.734
IN AN ATTEMPT
TO SHOW CORY

04:53.734 --> 04:57.133
THAT PHYSICAL APPEARANCE
IS SECONDARY
TO INNER BEAUTY.

04:58.667 --> 05:00.700
AHA. WELL, IN THAT CASE,
MISS LAWRENCE,

05:00.700 --> 05:04.800
I APPLAUD
YOUR ATTEMPT AT TEACHING
A VERY VALUABLE LESSON

05:04.800 --> 05:07.500
DURING THESE
EXTREMELY VULNERABLE...

05:07.500 --> 05:08.500
TEENAGE YEARS.

05:08.500 --> 05:10.467
YOU THINK I'M UGLY!

05:14.033 --> 05:16.800
NICE GOING,
FEENY.

05:19.300 --> 05:21.133
MAN COMING IN.
MAN COMING IN.

05:21.133 --> 05:23.767
I'M NOT LOOKING. I'M
JUST HERE ON BUSINESS.

05:23.767 --> 05:25.033
NOW I'M TAKING
MY ARM DOWN.

05:25.033 --> 05:26.567
YOU'LL PROBABLY
WANT TO SCATTER.

05:26.567 --> 05:28.700
GO AHEAD.
SCREAM. SCATTER.

05:28.700 --> 05:30.834
MAKE A BIG SCENE.

05:32.133 --> 05:34.667
SEE, 'CAUSE I'M A BOY.

05:35.800 --> 05:39.000
HEY, HOW COME YOU GUYS
GET A COUCH?

05:39.000 --> 05:41.000
SOMETIMES WE NEED
TO LIE DOWN.

05:41.000 --> 05:42.767
YOU SEE, THAT'S WHERE GUYS
ARE DIFFERENT.

05:42.767 --> 05:44.500
WE'RE IN, WE'RE OUT.
WE DON'T LIKE TO LINGER.

05:44.500 --> 05:47.233
LOOK, CORY, I'M HAVING
SOME PROBLEMS RIGHT NOW,

05:47.233 --> 05:49.967
AND I'D REALLY
LIKE TO BE ALONE.

05:49.967 --> 05:52.200
WELL, I'LL...

05:52.200 --> 05:54.367
BE ALONE WITH YOU.

05:58.500 --> 06:01.967
LOOK, YOU DON'T
HAVE ANY PROBLEMS.

06:01.967 --> 06:02.967
I MEAN...

06:02.967 --> 06:05.133
LOOK AT YOURSELF
IN THE MIRROR.

06:05.133 --> 06:06.367
YOU'RE
STILL BEAUTIFUL.

06:06.367 --> 06:07.734
I CAN'T LOOK
IN THE MIRROR.

06:07.734 --> 06:09.100
TOPANGA,
YOU WERE RIGHT.

06:09.100 --> 06:11.300
IT DOESN'T
MATTER TO ME
WHAT YOU LOOK LIKE.

06:11.300 --> 06:13.567
IT ONLY MATTERS
TO ME WHO YOU ARE.

06:13.567 --> 06:15.100
SEE, THAT'S
MY PROBLEM, CORY.

06:15.100 --> 06:18.934
I THOUGHT I WAS
SOMEONE WHO THOUGHT THAT
APPEARANCE DIDN'T MATTER,

06:18.934 --> 06:20.900
BUT THAT WAS ONLY BECAUSE
I WAS COMFORTABLE

06:20.900 --> 06:23.300
WITH MY APPEARANCE
ALL THIS TIME.

06:23.300 --> 06:24.667
BUT NOW I'M NOT.

06:24.667 --> 06:26.800
HOW SHALLOW CAN I BE?

06:26.800 --> 06:28.834
YOU ARE NOT SHALLOW.

06:28.834 --> 06:29.834
YOU'RE DEEP.

06:29.834 --> 06:31.100
YOU'RE THE DEEPEST,

06:31.100 --> 06:33.467
MOST THOUGHTFUL,
PROFOUND PERSON
I'VE EVER KNOWN.

06:33.467 --> 06:34.800
HOW'S MY HAIR LOOK?

06:34.800 --> 06:38.500
WELL, THAT'S NOT ONE
OF YOUR STRONG POINTS
ANYMORE.

06:38.500 --> 06:41.200
YOU GOTTA LET THAT GO.

06:44.300 --> 06:45.600
LOOK, HOW LONG
DID IT TAKE YOU

06:45.600 --> 06:47.133
TO GROW YOUR HAIR
THAT LONG?

06:47.133 --> 06:48.467
SIX OR SEVEN YEARS.

06:48.467 --> 06:50.700
THAT'S PERFECT

06:50.700 --> 06:52.000
BECAUSE IN SIX
OR SEVEN YEARS,

06:52.000 --> 06:53.300
YOU'LL GROW
YOUR HAIR BACK,

06:53.300 --> 06:55.500
I'LL BE OUT
OF MY GOOSEY-GOOSEY STAGE.

06:55.500 --> 06:56.800
DON'T YOU SEE?

06:56.800 --> 06:58.567
IT MAKES US EVEN CLOSER
AS A COUPLE

06:58.567 --> 07:01.567
BECAUSE NOW
WE ARE IN PERFECT SYNC.

07:02.600 --> 07:04.133
SEE, CORY.

07:04.133 --> 07:05.967
THAT'S WHY
I LOVE YOU.

07:05.967 --> 07:07.100
THANKS.
TODAY AFTER SCHOOL,

07:07.100 --> 07:08.367
I'LL GO DOWN TO
THE BEAUTY PARLOR

07:08.367 --> 07:09.500
AND GET THIS
ALL EVENED OUT.

07:09.500 --> 07:11.100
GREAT IDEA.

07:19.934 --> 07:21.200
SO, HOW'D IT GO?

07:21.200 --> 07:23.900
TOPANGA'S GOING
TO THE BEAUTY PARLOR
AFTER SCHOOL.

07:23.900 --> 07:24.900
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

07:24.900 --> 07:27.834
HUH. SO WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO NOW?

07:27.834 --> 07:29.033
I DON'T KNOW.

07:29.033 --> 07:30.934
WANNA SIT
ON THE COUCH?

07:30.934 --> 07:32.600
YEAH.

07:43.967 --> 07:45.667
AHH.

07:45.667 --> 07:47.400
HA HA.
YOU SOLVED THAT CRIME,

07:47.400 --> 07:49.500
YOU FAT, FAT MAN.

07:51.967 --> 07:53.967
ERIC, IT'S 4:00.

07:53.967 --> 07:56.467
YOU WERE SITTING THERE
WHEN I LEFT THIS MORNING.

07:56.467 --> 07:59.000
YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO LOOK FOR A JOB.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.800
THINK I FOUND ONE, MOM.
CHECK IT OUT.

08:00.800 --> 08:03.000
ALL DAY LONG, I'VE BEEN
WATCHING CRIMES ON TV

08:03.000 --> 08:05.734
SOLVED BY OLD GUYS,
BY FAT GUYS,

08:05.734 --> 08:07.400
BY GUYS WITH
WRINKLED RAINCOATS.

08:07.400 --> 08:08.900
SO, NATURALLY,
IT OCCURS TO ME,

08:08.900 --> 08:14.000
WHAT THIS WORLD NEEDS
IS "ERIC MATTHEWS,
GOOD-LOOKING DETECTIVE."

08:14.000 --> 08:16.967
I'M GONNA DO
SO MUCH HOMEWORK.

08:16.967 --> 08:19.133
CHECK IT OUT.
I ALREADY THOUGHT
OF A THEME SONG.

